{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e1f26ddd-3421-4786-bd84-d2d8f6b11012","content":"Here are the three breaking changes and their fixes:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `Buffer.cs` — `[InlineArray]` on `record struct` is now illegal\n\nC# 13 disallows `[InlineArray]` on `record struct` types (the compiler-synthesized `Equals`/`GetHashCode` don't make sense for inline arrays).\n\n**Fix:** Use a plain `struct`:\n\n```csharp\n[System.Runtime.CompilerServices.InlineArray(10)]\nstruct Buffer\n{\n    private int _element0;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `Generator.cs` — `stackalloc` in a local function inside an iterator\n\nC# 13 now permits `unsafe` code directly in iterators/async methods. A side effect is that the compiler reanalyzes local functions containing `stackalloc` within iterator methods and now raises an error, since `stackalloc` cannot survive across `yield` suspension points in the state machine.\n\n**Fix:** Extract the local function to a regular static method:\n\n```csharp\nunsafe class DataGenerator\n{\n    IEnumerable<int> Generate()\n    {\n        yield return 1;\n        Process();\n    }\n\n    static void Process()\n    {\n        int* p = stackalloc int[10];\n        // ... work with pointer\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `Resolver.cs` — Overload resolution ambiguity with collection expressions\n\nC# 13 improved collection expression conversions so that `[]` is now convertible to both `ReadOnlySpan<int>` **and** `Span<object>`. In C# 12, only one overload was applicable, so it compiled. Now it's ambiguous.\n\n**Fix:** Disambiguate with an explicit type:\n\n```csharp\nstatic void Main()\n{\n    Process(ReadOnlySpan<int>.Empty);\n    // or: Process((ReadOnlySpan<int>)[]);\n}\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d2506a25-8a54-46f1-a35a-456db747a0b4","outputTokens":466,"requestId":"6C24:2F2FF8:18ED2BC:1C509D6:69FE8D46"},"id":"7e672a83-e44d-4c39-9901-9118c947a769","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:26:40.407Z","parentId":"2c6540a3-eef1-420d-b9e8-a2af91b6b623"}
